The paper proposes a novel swarm intelligent algorithm that is based on particle swarm optimization (PSO) and inspired by the bee swarming reproductive process. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Additionally, the algorithm is designed to optimize search agents' position during both the exploration and exploitation phases, which suggests that it could also belong to the Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-category. Finally, the paper applies the algorithm to real-world applications, indicating that it could also belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category.
